On 11/13/2012 8:26 PM, John Kolak wrote:
> If the pedal is adjusted correctly, the clutch is slipping, so you
> most likely need a new pressure plate, or your disc is worn way thin.
> Actually, with that much slip, I don't think you could drive.

I concur.  The only way you could possibly get it to slip that much is 
if you tightened to clutch cable so tight that it's always actuating the 
pressure plate, and you probably wouldn't be able to do that as there 
isn't enough thread on the end of the cable to pull it that tight.
